w this is the basis for judging: that the light has come into the world and people loved the darkness rather than the light, because their deeds were evil."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"3","verse":"20","text":"For everyone who does evil deeds hates the light and does not come to the light, so that their deeds will not be exposed."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"3","verse":"21","text":"But the one who practices the truth comes to the light, so that it may be plainly evident that his deeds have been done in God.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"3","verse":"22","text":" After this, Jesus and his disciples came into Judean territory, and there he spent time with them and was baptizing."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"3","verse":"23","text":"John was also baptizing at Aenon near Salim, because water was plentiful there, and people were coming to him and being baptized."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"3","verse":"24","text":"(For John had not yet been thrown into prison.)<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"3","verse":"25","text":" Now a dispute came about between some of John\u2019s disciples and a certain Jew concerning ceremonial washing."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"3","verse":"26","text":"So they came to John and said to him, \u201cRabbi, the one who was with you on the other side of the Jordan River, about whom you testified – see, he is baptizing, and everyone is flocking to him!\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"3","verse":"27","text":" John replied, \u201cNo one can receive anything unless it has been given to him from heaven."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"3","verse":"28","text":"You yourselves can testify that I said, \u2018I am not the Christ,\u2019 but rather, \u2018I have been sent before him.\u2019"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"3","verse":"29","text":"The one who has the bride is the bridegroom. The friend of the bridegroom, who stands by and listens for him, rejoices greatly when he hears the bridegroom\u2019s voice. This then is my j