":"4","verse":"29","text":"\u201cCome, see a man who told me everything I ever did. Surely he can\u2019t be the Messiah, can he?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"30","text":"So they left the town and began coming to him.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"31","text":" Meanwhile the disciples were urging him, \u201cRabbi, eat something.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"32","text":"But he said to them, \u201cI have food to eat that you know nothing about.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"33","text":"So the disciples began to say to one another, \u201cNo one brought him anything to eat, did they?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"34","text":"Jesus said to them, \u201cMy food is to do the will of the one who sent me and to complete his work."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"35","text":"Don\u2019t you say, \u2018There are four more months and then comes the harvest?\u2019 I tell you, look up and see that the fields are already white for harvest!"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"36","text":"The one who reaps receives pay and gathers fruit for eternal life, so that the one who sows and the one who reaps can rejoice together."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"37","text":"For in this instance the saying is true, \u2018One sows and another reaps.\u2019"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"38","text":"I sent you to reap what you did not work for; others have labored and you have entered into their labor.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"39","text":" Now many Samaritans from that town believed in him because of the report of the woman who testified, \u201cHe told me everything I ever did.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"40","text":"So when the Samaritans came to him, they began asking him to stay with them. He stayed there two days,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"41","text":"and because of his word many more believed."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"42","text":"They said to the woman, \u201cNo longer do we believe because of your words, for we have heard for ourselves, and we know that this one really is the Savior of the world.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"43","text":" After the two days he departed from there to Galilee."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"44","text":"(For Jesus himself had testified that a prophet has no honor in his own country.)"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"45","text":"So when he came to Galilee, the Galileans welcomed him because they had seen all the things he had done in Jerusalem at the feast (for they themselves had gone to the feast).<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"46","text":" Now he came again to Cana in Galilee where he had made the water wine. In Capernaum there was a certain royal official whose son was sick."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"47","text":"When he heard that Jesus had come back from Judea to Galilee, he went to him and begged him to come down and heal his son, who was about to die."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"48","text":"So Jesus said to him, \u201cUnless you people see signs and wonders you will never believe!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"49","text":"\u201cSir,\u201d the official said to him, \u201ccome down before my child dies.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"50","text":"Jesus told him, \u201cGo home; your son will live.\u201d The man believed the word that Jesus spoke to him, and set off for home.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"51","text":" While he was on his way down, his slaves met him and told him that his son was going to live."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"52","text":"So he asked them the time when his condition began to improve, and they told him, \u201cYesterday at one o\u2019clock in the afternoon the fever left him.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"53","text":"Then the father realized that it was the very time Jesus had said to him, \u201cYour son will live,\u201d and he himself believed along with his entire household."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"4","verse":"54","text":"Jesus did this as his second miraculous sign when he returned from Judea to Galilee.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"1","text":" After this there was a Jewish feast, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"2","text":"Now there is in Jerusalem by the Sheep Gate a pool called Bethzatha<\/i> in Aramaic, which has five covered walkways."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"3","text":"A great number of sick, blind, lame, and paralyzed people were lying in these walkways."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"4","text":"[[EMPTY]]"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"5","text":"Now a man was there who had been disabled for thirty-eight years."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"6","text":"When Jesus saw him lying there and when he realized that the man had been disabled a long time already, he said to him, \u201cDo you want to become well?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"7","text":"The sick man answered him, \u201cSir, I have no one to put me into the pool when the water is stirred up. While I am trying to get into the water, someone else goes down there before me.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"8","text":"Jesus said to him, \u201cStand up! Pick up your mat and walk.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"9","text":"Immediately the man was healed, and he picked up his mat and started walking. (Now that day was a Sabbath.)<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"10","text":" So the Jewish leaders said to the man who had been healed, \u201cIt is the Sabbath, and you are not permitted to carry your mat.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"11","text":"But he answered them, \u201cThe man who made me well said to me, \u2018Pick up your mat and walk.\u2019\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"12","text":"They asked him, \u201cWho is the man who said to you, \u2018Pick up your mat and walk\u2019?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"13","text":"But the man who had been healed did not know who it was, for Jesus had slipped out, since there was a crowd in that place.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"14","text":" After this Jesus found him at the temple and said to him, \u201cLook, you have become well. Don\u2019t sin any more, lest anything worse happen to you.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"15","text":"The man went away and informed the Jewish leaders that Jesus was the one who had made him well.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"16","text":" Now because Jesus was doing these things on the Sabbath, the Jewish leaders began persecuting him."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"17","text":"So he told them, \u201cMy Father is working until now, and I too am working.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"18","text":"For this reason the Jewish leaders were trying even harder to kill him, because not only was he breaking the Sabbath, but he was also calling God his own Father, thus making himself equal with God.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"19","text":" So Jesus answered them, \u201cI tell you the solemn truth, the Son can do nothing on his own initiative, but only what he sees the Father doing. For whatever the Father does, the Son does likewise."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"20","text":"For the Father loves the Son and shows him everything he does, and will show him greater deeds than these, so that you will be amazed."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"21","text":"For just as the Father raises the dead and gives them life, so also the Son gives life to whomever he wishes."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"22","text":"Furthermore, the Father does not judge anyone, but has assigned all judgment to the Son,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"23","text":"so that all people will honor the Son just as they honor the Father. The one who does not honor the Son does not honor the Father who sent him.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"24","text":" \u201cI tell you the solemn truth, the one who hears my message and believes the one who sent me has eternal life and will not be condemned, but has crossed over from death to life."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"25","text":"I tell you the solemn truth, a time is coming – and is now here – when the dead will hear the voice of the Son of God, and those who hear will live."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"26","text":"For just as the Father has life in himself, thus he has granted the Son to have life in himself,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"27","text":"and he has granted the Son authority to execute judgment, because he is the Son of Man.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"28","text":" \u201cDo not be amazed at this, because a time is coming when all who are in the tombs will hear his voice"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"29","text":"and will come out – the ones who have done what is good to the resurrection resulting in life, and the ones who have done what is evil to the resurrection resulting in condemnation."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"30","text":"I can do nothing on my own initiative. Just as I hear, I judge, and my judgment is just, because I do not seek my own will, but the will of the one who sent me.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"31","text":" \u201cIf I testify about myself, my testimony is not true."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"32","text":"There is another who testifies about me, and I know the testimony he testifies about me is true."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":