u is Moses, in whom you have placed your hope."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"46","text":"If you believed Moses, you would believe me, because he wrote about me."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"5","verse":"47","text":"But if you do not believe what Moses wrote, how will you believe my words?\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"1","text":" After this Jesus went away to the other side of the Sea of Galilee (also called the Sea of Tiberias)."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"2","text":"A large crowd was following him because they were observing the miraculous signs he was performing on the sick."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"3","text":"So Jesus went on up the mountainside and sat down there with his disciples."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"4","text":"(Now the Jewish feast of the Passover was near.)"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"5","text":"Then Jesus, when he looked up and saw that a large crowd was coming to him, said to Philip, \u201cWhere can we buy bread so that these people may eat?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"6","text":"(Now Jesus said this to test him, for he knew what he was going to do.)"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"7","text":"Philip replied, \u201cTwo hundred silver coins worth of bread would not be enough for them, for each one to get a little.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"8","text":"One of Jesus\u2019 disciples, Andrew, Simon Peter\u2019s brother, said to him,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"9","text":"\u201cHere is a boy who has five barley loaves and two fish, but what good are these for so many people?\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"10","text":" Jesus said, \u201cHave the people sit down.\u201d (Now there was a lot of grass in that place.) So the men sat down, about five thousand in number."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"11","text":"Then Jesus took the loaves, and when he had given thanks, he distributed the bread to those who were seated. He then did the same with the fish, as much as they wanted."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"12","text":"When they were all satisfied, Jesus said to his disciples, \u201cGather up the broken pieces that are left over, so that nothing is wasted.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"13","text":"So they gathered them up and filled twelve baskets with broken pieces from the five barley loaves left over by the people who had eaten.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"14","text":" Now when the people saw the miraculous sign that Jesus performed, they began to say to one another, \u201cThis is certainly the Prophet<\/i> who is to come into the world<\/i>.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"15","text":"Then Jesus, because he knew they were going to come and seize him by force to make him king, withdrew again up the mountainside alone.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"16","text":" Now when evening came, his disciples went down to the lake,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"17","text":"got into a boat, and started to cross the lake to Capernaum. (It had already become dark, and Jesus had not yet come to them.)"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"18","text":"By now a strong wind was blowing and the sea was getting rough."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"19","text":"Then, when they had rowed about three or four miles, they caught sight of Jesus walking on the lake, approaching the boat, and they were frightened."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"20","text":"But he said to them, \u201cIt is I. Do not be afraid.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"21","text":"Then they wanted to take him into the boat, and immediately the boat came to the land where they had been heading.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"22","text":" The next day the crowd that remained on the other side of the lake realized that only one small boat had been there, and that Jesus had not boarded it with his disciples, but that his disciples had gone away alone."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"23","text":"But some boats from Tiberias came to shore near the place where they had eaten the bread after the Lord had given thanks."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"24","text":"So when the crowd realized that neither Jesus nor his disciples were there, they got into the boats and came to Capernaum looking for Jesus.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"25","text":" When they found him on the other side of the lake, they said to him, \u201cRabbi, when did you get here?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"26","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cI tell you the solemn truth, you are looking for me not because you saw miraculous signs, but because you ate all the loaves of bread you wanted."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"27","text":"Do not work for the food that disappears, but for the food that remains to eternal life – the food which the Son of Man will give to you. For God the Father has put his seal of approval on him.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"28","text":" So then they said to him, \u201cWhat must we do to accomplish the deeds God requires?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"29","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cThis is the deed God requires – to believe in the one whom he sent.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"30","text":"So they said to him, \u201cThen what miraculous sign will you perform, so that we may see it and believe you? What will you do?"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"31","text":"Our ancestors ate the manna in the wilderness, just as it is written, \u2018He gave them bread from heaven to eat<\/i><\/b>.\u2019\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"32","text":" Then Jesus told them, \u201cI tell you the solemn truth, it is not Moses who has given you the bread from heaven, but my Father is giving you the true bread from heaven."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"33","text":"For the bread of God is the one who comes down from heaven and gives life to the world.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"34","text":"So they said to him, \u201cSir, give us this bread all the time!\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"35","text":" Jesus said to them, \u201cI am the bread of life. The one who comes to me will never go hungry, and the one who believes in me will never be thirsty."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"36","text":"But I told you that you have seen me and still do not believe."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"37","text":"Everyone whom the Father gives me will come to me, and the one who comes to me I will never send away."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"38","text":"For I have come down from heaven not to do my own will but the will of the one who sent me."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"39","text":"Now this is the will of the one who sent me – that I should not lose one person of every one he has given me, but raise them all up at the last day."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"40","text":"For this is the will of my Father – for everyone who looks on the Son and believes in him to have eternal life, and I will raise him up at the last day.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"41","text":" Then the Jews who were hostile to Jesus began complaining about him because he said, \u201cI am the bread that came down from heaven,\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"42","text":"and they said, \u201cIsn\u2019t this Jesus the son of Joseph, whose father and mother we know? How can he now say, \u2018I have come down from heaven\u2019?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"6","verse":"43","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cDo not complain about me to one another."},{"bookname":"John","chap