nt up, not openly but in secret."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"11","text":"So the Jewish leaders were looking for him at the feast, asking, \u201cWhere is he?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"12","text":"There was a lot of grumbling about him among the crowds. Some were saying, \u201cHe is a good man,\u201d but others, \u201cHe deceives the common people.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"13","text":"However, no one spoke openly about him for fear of the Jewish leaders.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"14","text":" When the feast was half over, Jesus went up to the temple courts and began to teach."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"15","text":"Then the Jewish leaders were astonished and said, \u201cHow does this man know so much when he has never had formal instruction?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"16","text":"So Jesus replied, \u201cMy teaching is not from me, but from the one who sent me."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"17","text":"If anyone wants to do God\u2019s will, he will know about my teaching, whether it is from God or whether I speak from my own authority."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"18","text":"The person who speaks on his own authority desires to receive honor for himself; the one who desires the honor of the one who sent him is a man of integrity, and there is no unrighteousness in him."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"19","text":"Hasn\u2019t Moses given you the law? Yet not one of you keeps the law! Why do you want to kill me?\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"20","text":" The crowd answered, \u201cYou\u2019re possessed by a demon! Who is trying to kill you?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"21","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cI performed one miracle and you are all amazed."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"22","text":"However, because Moses gave you the practice of circumcision (not that it came from Moses, but from the forefathers), you circumcise a male child on the Sabbath."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"23","text":"But if a male child is circumcised on the Sabbath so that the law of Moses is not broken, why are you angry with me because I made a man completely well on the Sabbath?"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"24","text":"Do not judge according to external appearance, but judge with proper judgment.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"25","text":" Then some of the residents of Jerusalem began to say, \u201cIsn\u2019t this the man they are trying to kill?"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"26","text":"Yet here he is, speaking publicly, and they are saying nothing to him. Do the rulers really know that this man is the Christ?"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"27","text":"But we know where this man comes from. Whenever the Christ comes, no one will know where he comes from.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"28","text":" Then Jesus, while teaching in the temple courts, cried out, \u201cYou both know me and know where I come from! And I have not come on my own initiative, but the one who sent me is true. You do not know him,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"29","text":"but I know him, because I have come from him and he sent me.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"30","text":" So then they tried to seize Jesus, but no one laid a hand on him, because his time had not yet come."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"31","text":"Yet many of the crowd believed in him and said, \u201cWhenever the Christ comes, he won\u2019t perform more miraculous signs than this man did, will he?\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"32","text":" The Pharisees heard the crowd murmuring these things about Jesus, so the chief priests and the Pharisees sent officers to arrest him."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"33","text":"Then Jesus said, \u201cI will be with you for only a little while longer, and then I am going to the one who sent me."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"34","text":"You will look for me but will not find me, and where I am you cannot come.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"35","text":" Then the Jewish leaders said to one another, \u201cWhere is he going to go that we cannot find him? He is not going to go to the Jewish people dispersed among the Greeks and teach the Greeks, is he?"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"36","text":"What did he mean by saying, \u2018You will look for me but will not find me, and where I am you cannot come\u2019?\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"37","text":" On the last day of the feast, the greatest day, Jesus stood up and shouted out, \u201cIf anyone is thirsty, let him come to me, and"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"38","text":"let the one who believes in me drink. Just as the scripture says, \u2018From within him<\/i><\/b> will flow rivers of living water<\/i><\/b>.\u2019\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"39","text":"(Now he said this about the Spirit, whom those who believed in him were going to receive, for the Spirit had not yet been given, because Jesus was not yet glorified.)<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"40","text":" When they heard these words, some of the crowd began to say, \u201cThis really is the Prophet!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"41","text":"Others said, \u201cThis is the Christ!\u201d But still others said, \u201cNo, for the Christ doesn\u2019t come from Galilee, does he?"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"42","text":"Don\u2019t the scriptures say that the Christ is a descendant<\/i> of David<\/i> and comes from Bethlehem<\/i>, the village where David lived?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"7","verse":"43","text":"So there was a division in the crowd because of Jesus."}