 woman was caught in the very act of adultery."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"5","text":"In the law Moses commanded us to stone to death<\/i> such women. What then do you say?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"6","text":"(Now they were asking this in an attempt to trap him, so that they could bring charges against him.) Jesus bent down and wrote on the ground with his finger."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"7","text":"When they persisted in asking him, he stood up straight and replied, \u201cWhoever among you is guiltless may be the first to throw a stone at her.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"8","text":"Then he bent over again and wrote on the ground.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"9","text":" Now when they heard this, they began to drift away one at a time, starting with the older ones, until Jesus was left alone with the woman standing before him."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"10","text":"Jesus stood up straight and said to her, \u201cWoman, where are they? Did no one condemn you?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"11","text":"She replied, \u201cNo one, Lord.\u201d And Jesus said, \u201cI do not condemn you either. Go, and from now on do not sin any more.\u201d]]<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"12","text":" Then Jesus spoke out again, \u201cI am the light of the world. The one who follows me will never walk in darkness, but will have the light of life.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"13","text":"So the Pharisees objected, \u201cYou testify about yourself; your testimony is not true!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"14","text":"Jesus answered, \u201cEven if I testify about myself, my testimony is true, because I know where I came from and where I am going. But you people do not know where I came from or where I am going."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"15","text":"You people judge by outward appearances; I do not judge anyone."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"16","text":"But if I judge, my evaluation is accurate, because I am not alone when I judge, but I and the Father who sent me do so together."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"17","text":"It is written in your law that the testimony of two men is true<\/i>."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"18","text":"I testify about myself and the Father who sent me testifies about me.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"19","text":" Then they began asking him, \u201cWho is your father?\u201d Jesus answered, \u201cYou do not know either me or my Father. If you knew me you would know my Father too.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"20","text":"(Jesus spoke these words near the offering box while he was teaching in the temple courts. No one seized him because his time had not yet come.)<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"21","text":" Then Jesus said to them again, \u201cI am going away, and you will look for me but will die in your sin. Where I am going you cannot come.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"22","text":"So the Jewish leaders began to say, \u201cPerhaps he is going to kill himself, because he says, \u2018Where I am going you cannot come.\u2019\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"23","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cYou people are from below; I am from above. You people are from this world; I am not from this world."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"24","text":"Thus I told you that you will die in your sins. For unless you believe that I am he, you will die in your sins.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"25","text":" So they said to him, \u201cWho are you?\u201d Jesus replied, \u201cWhat I have told you from the beginning."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"8","verse":"26","text":"I have many things to say and to judge about you, but the Father who sent me is truthful, and the t