yet you presume to teach us?\u201d So they threw him out.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"9","verse":"35","text":" Jesus heard that they had thrown him out, so he found the man and said to him, \u201cDo you believe in the Son of Man?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"9","verse":"36","text":"The man replied, \u201cAnd who is he, sir, that I may believe in him?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"9","verse":"37","text":"Jesus told him, \u201cYou have seen him; he is the one speaking with you.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"9","verse":"38","text":"[He said, \u201cLord, I believe,\u201d and he worshiped him."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"9","verse":"39","text":"Jesus said,] \u201cFor judgment I have come into this world, so that those who do not see may gain their sight, and the ones who see may become blind.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"9","verse":"40","text":" Some of the Pharisees who were with him heard this and asked him, \u201cWe are not blind too, are we?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"9","verse":"41","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cIf you were blind, you would not be guilty of sin, but now because you claim that you can see, your guilt remains.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"1","text":" \u201cI tell you the solemn truth, the one who does not enter the sheepfold by the door, but climbs in some other way, is a thief and a robber."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"2","text":"The one who enters by the door is the shepherd of the sheep."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"3","text":"The doorkeeper opens the door for him, and the sheep hear his voice. He calls his own sheep by name and leads them out."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"4","text":"When he has brought all his own sheep out, he goes ahead of them, and the sheep follow him because they recognize his voice."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"5","text":"They will never follow a stranger, but will run away from him, because they do not recognize the stranger\u2019s voice.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"6","text":"Jesus told them this parable, but they did not understand what he was saying to them.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"7","text":" So Jesus said to them again, \u201cI tell you the solemn truth, I am the door for the sheep."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"8","text":"All who came before me were thieves and robbers, but the sheep did not listen to them."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"9","text":"I am the door. If anyone enters through me, he will be saved, and will come in and go out, and find pasture."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"10","text":"The thief comes only to steal and kill and destroy; I have come so that they may have life, and may have it abundantly.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"11","text":" \u201cI am the good shepherd. The good shepherd lays down his life for the sheep."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"12","text":"The hired hand, who is not a shepherd and does not own sheep, sees the wolf coming and abandons the sheep and runs away. So the wolf attacks the sheep and scatters them."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"13","text":"Because he is a hired hand and is not concerned about the sheep, he runs away.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"14","text":" \u201cI am the good shepherd. I know my own and my own know me –"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"15","text":"just as the Father knows me and I know the Father – and I lay down my life for the sheep."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"16","text":"I have other sheep that do not come from this sheepfold. I must bring them too, and they will listen to my voice, so that there will be one flock and one shepherd."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"17","text":"This is why the Father loves me – because I lay down my life, so that I may take it back again."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"18","text":"No one takes it away from me, but I lay it down of my own free will. I have the authority to lay it down, and I have the authority to take it back again. This commandment I received from my Father.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"19","text":" Another sharp division took place among the Jewish people because of these words."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"20","text":"Many of them were saying, \u201cHe is possessed by a demon and has lost his mind! Why do you listen to him?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"21","text":"Others said, \u201cThese are not the words of someone possessed by a demon. A demon cannot cause the blind to see, can it?\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"22","text":" Then came the feast of the Dedication in Jerusalem."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"23","text":"It was winter, and Jesus was walking in the temple area in Solomon\u2019s Portico."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"24","text":"The Jewish leaders surrounded him and asked, \u201cHow long will you keep us in suspense? If you are the Christ, tell us plainly.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"25","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cI told you and you do not believe. The deeds I do in my Father\u2019s name testify about me."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"26","text":"But you refuse to believe because you are not my sheep."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"27","text":"My sheep listen to my voice, and I know them, and they follow me."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"28","text":"I give them eternal life, and they will never perish; no one will snatch them from my hand."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"29","text":"My Father, who has given them to me, is greater than all, and no one can snatch them from my Father\u2019s hand."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"10","verse":"30","t