red a dinner for Jesus there. Martha was serving, and Lazarus was among those present at the table with him."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"3","text":"Then Mary took three quarters of a pound of expensive aromatic oil from pure nard and anointed the feet of Jesus. She then wiped his feet dry with her hair. (Now the house was filled with the fragrance of the perfumed oil.)"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"4","text":"But Judas Iscariot, one of his disciples (the one who was going to betray him) said,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"5","text":"\u201cWhy wasn\u2019t this oil sold for three hundred silver coins and the money given to the poor?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"6","text":"(Now Judas said this not because he was concerned about the poor, but because he was a thief. As keeper of the money box, he used to steal what was put into it.)"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"7","text":"So Jesus said, \u201cLeave her alone. She has kept it for the day of my burial."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"8","text":"For you will always have the poor with you, but you will not always have me!\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"9","text":" Now a large crowd of Judeans learned that Jesus was there, and so they came not only because of him but also to see Lazarus whom he had raised from the dead."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"10","text":"So the chief priests planned to kill Lazarus too,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"11","text":"for on account of him many of the Jewish people from Jerusalem were going away and believing in Jesus.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"12","text":" The next day the large crowd that had come to the feast heard that Jesus was coming to Jerusalem."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"13","text":"So they took branches of palm trees and went out to meet him. They began to shout, \u201cHosanna!<\/i><\/b> Bl