now where he is going."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"36","text":"While you have the light, believe in the light, so that you may become sons of light.\u201d When Jesus had said these things, he went away and hid himself from them.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"37","text":" Although Jesus had performed so many miraculous signs before them, they still refused to believe in him,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"38","text":"so that the word of Isaiah the prophet would be fulfilled. He said, \u201cLord, who has believed our message, and to whom has the arm of the Lord<\/i><\/b> been revealed?<\/i><\/b>\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"39","text":"For this reason they could not believe, because again Isaiah said,<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"40","text":" \u201cHe has blinded their eyes<\/i><\/b><\/p> and hardened their heart,<\/i><\/b><\/p> so that they would not see with their eyes<\/i><\/b><\/p> and understand with their heart,<\/i><\/b><\/p> and turn to me,<\/i><\/b> and I would heal them<\/b>.<\/i>\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"41","text":" Isaiah said these things because he saw Christ\u2019s glory, and spoke about him.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"42","text":" Nevertheless, even among the rulers many believed in him, but because of the Pharisees they would not confess Jesus to be the Christ, so that they would not be put out of the synagogue."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"43","text":"For they loved praise from men more than praise from God.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"44","text":" But Jesus shouted out, \u201cThe one who believes in me does not believe in me, but in the one who sent me,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"45","text":"and the one who sees me sees the one who sent me."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"46","text":"I have come as a light into the world, so that everyone who believes in me should not remain in darkness."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"47","text":"If anyone hears my words and does not obey them, I do not judge him. For I have not come to judge the world, but to save the world."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"48","text":"The one who rejects me and does not accept my words has a judge; the word I have spoken will judge him at the last day."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"49","text":"For I have not spoken from my own authority, but the Father himself who sent me has commanded me what I should say and what I should speak."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"12","verse":"50","text":"And I know that his commandment is eternal life. Thus the things I say, I say just as the Father has told me.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"1","text":" Just before the Passover feast, Jesus knew that his time had come to depart from this world to the Father. Having loved his own who were in the world, he now loved them to the very end."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"2","text":"The evening meal was in progress, and the devil had already put into the heart of Judas Iscariot, Simon\u2019s son, that he should betray Jesus."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"3","text":"Because Jesus knew that the Father had handed all things over to him, and that he had come from God and was going back to God,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"4","text":"he got up from the meal, removed his outer clothes, took a towel and tied it around himself."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"5","text":"He poured water into the washbasin and began to wash the disciples\u2019 feet and to dry them with the towel he had wrapped around himself.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"6","text":" Then he came to Simon Peter. Peter said to him, \u201cLord, are you going to wash my feet?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"7","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cYou do not understand what I am doing now, but you will understand after these things.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"8","text":"Peter said to him, \u201cYou will never wash my feet!\u201d Jesus replied, \u201cIf I do not wash you, you have no share with me.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"9","text":"Simon Peter said to him, \u201cLord, wash not only my feet, but also my hands and my head!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"10","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cThe one who has bathed needs only to wash his feet, but is completely clean. And you disciples are clean, but not every one of you.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"11","text":"(For Jesus knew the one who was going to betray him. For this reason he said, \u201cNot every one of you is clean.\u201d)<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"12","text":" So when Jesus had washed their feet and put his outer clothing back on, he took his place at the table again and said to them, \u201cDo you understand what I have done for you?"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"13","text":"You call me \u2018Teacher\u2019 and \u2018Lord,\u2019 and do so correctly, for that is what I am."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"14","text":"If I then, your Lord and Teacher, have washed your feet, you too ought to wash one another\u2019s feet."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"15","text":"For I have given you an example – you should do just as I have done for you."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"16","text":"I tell you the solemn truth, the slave is not greater than his master, nor is the one who is sent as a messenger greater than the one who sent him."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"17","text":"If you understand these things, you will be blessed if you do them.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"18","text":" \u201cWhat I am saying does not refer to all of you. I know the ones I have chosen. But this is to fulfill the scripture, \u2018The one who eats my bread<\/i><\/b> has turned against me<\/i><\/b>.\u2019"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"19","text":"I am telling you this now, before it happens, so that when it happens you may believe that I am he."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"20","text":"I tell you the solemn truth, whoever accepts the one I send accepts me, and whoever accepts me accepts the one who sent me.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"21","text":" When he had said these things, Jesus was greatly distressed in spirit, and testified, \u201cI tell you the solemn truth, one of you will betray me.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"22","text":"The disciples began to look at one another, worried and perplexed to know which of them he was talking about."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"23","text":"One of his disciples, the one Jesus loved, was at the table to the right of Jesus in a place of honor."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"24","text":"So Simon Peter gestured to this disciple to ask Jesus who it was he was referring to."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"25","text":"Then the disciple whom Jesus loved leaned back against Jesus\u2019 chest and asked him, \u201cLord, who is it?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"26","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cIt is the one to whom I will give this piece of bread after I have dipped it in the dish.\u201d Then he dipped the piece of bread in the dish and gave it to Judas Iscariot, Simon\u2019s son."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"27","text":"And after Judas took the piece of bread, Satan entered into him. Jesus said to him, \u201cWhat you are about to do, do quickly.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"28","text":"(Now none of those present at the table understood why Jesus said this to Judas."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"29","text":"Some thought that, because Judas had the money box, Jesus was telling him to buy whatever they needed for the feast, or to give something to the poor.)"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"30","text":"Judas took the piece of bread and went out immediately. (Now it was night.)<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"31","text":" When Judas had gone out, Jesus said, \u201cNow the Son of Man is glorified, and God is glorified in him."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"32","text":"If God is glorified in him, God will also glorify him in himself, and he will glorify him right away."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"33","text":"Children, I am still with you for a little while. You will look for me, and just as I said to the Jewish religious leaders, \u2018Where I am going you cannot come,\u2019 now I tell you the same.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"34","text":" \u201cI give you a new commandment – to love one another. Just as I have loved you, you also are to love one another."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"35","text":"Everyone will know by this that you are my disciples – if you have love for one another.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"36","text":" Simon Peter said to him, \u201cLord, where are you going?\u201d Jesus replied, \u201cWhere I am going, you cannot follow me now, but you will follow later.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"37","text":"Peter said to him, \u201cLord, why can\u2019t I follow you now? I will lay down my life for you!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"13","verse":"38","text":"Jesus answered, \u201cWill you lay down your life for me? I tell you the solemn truth, the rooster will not crow until you have denied me three times!<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"14","verse":"1","text":" \u201cDo not let your hearts be distressed. You believe in God; believe also in me."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"14","verse":"2","text":"There are many dwelling places in my Father\u2019s house. Otherwise, I would have told you, because I am going away to make ready a place for you."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"14","verse":"3","text":"And if I go and make ready a place for you, I will come again and take you to be with me, so that where I am you may be too."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"14","verse":"4","text":"And you know the way where I am going.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"14","verse":"5","text":" Thomas said, \u201cLord, we don\u2019t know where you are going. How can we know the way?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"14","verse":"6","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cI am the way, and the truth, and the life. No one comes to the Father except through me."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"14","verse":"7","text":"If you have known me, you will know my Father too. And from now on you do know him and have seen him.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"14","verse":"8","text":" Philip said, \u201cLord, show us the Father, and we will be content.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"14","verse":"9","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cHave I been with you for so long, and you have not known me, Philip? The person who has seen me has seen the Father! How can you say, \u2018Show us the Father\u2019?"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"14","verse":"10","text":"Do you not believe that I am in the Father, and the Father is in me? The words that I say to you, I do not speak on my own initiative, but the Father residing in me performs his miraculous deeds."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"14","verse":"11","text":"Believe me that I am in the Father, and the Father is in me, but if you do not believe me, believe because of the miraculous deeds themselves."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"14","verse":"12","text":"I tell you the solemn truth, the person who believes in me will perform the miraculous deeds that I am doing, and will perform greater deeds than these, because I am going to the Father."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"