hat is to come."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"14","text":"He will glorify me, because he will receive from me what is mine and will tell it to you."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"15","text":"Everything that the Father has is mine; that is why I said the Spirit will receive from me what is mine and will tell it to you."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"16","text":"In a little while you will see me no longer; again after a little while, you will see me.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"17","text":" Then some of his disciples said to one another, \u201cWhat is the meaning of what he is saying, \u2018In a little while you will not see me; again after a little while, you will see me,\u2019 and, \u2018because I am going to the Father\u2019?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"18","text":"So they kept on repeating, \u201cWhat is the meaning of what he says, \u2018In a little while\u2019? We do not understand what he is talking about.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"19","text":" Jesus could see that they wanted to ask him about these things, so he said to them, \u201cAre you asking each other about this – that I said, \u2018In a little while you will not see me; again after a little while, you will see me\u2019?"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"20","text":"I tell you the solemn truth, you will weep and wail, but the world will rejoice; you will be sad, but your sadness will turn into joy."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"21","text":"When a woman gives birth, she has distress because her time has come, but when her child is born, she no longer remembers the suffering because of her joy that a human being has been born into the world."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"22","text":"So also you have sorrow now, but I will see you again, and your hearts will rejoice, and no one will take your joy away from you<\/i>."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"23","text":"At that time you will ask me nothing. I tell you the solemn truth, whatever you ask the Father in my name he will give you."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"24","text":"Until now you have not asked for anything in my name. Ask and you will receive it, so that your joy may be complete.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"25","text":" \u201cI have told you these things in obscure figures of speech; a time is coming when I will no longer speak to you in obscure figures, but will tell you plainly about the Father."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"26","text":"At that time you will ask in my name, and I do not say that I will ask the Father on your behalf."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"27","text":"For the Father himself loves you, because you have loved me and have believed that I came from God."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"28","text":"I came from the Father and entered into the world, but in turn, I am leaving the world and going back to the Father.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"29","text":" His disciples said, \u201cLook, now you are speaking plainly and not in obscure figures of speech!"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"30","text":"Now we know that you know everything and do not need anyone to ask you anything. Because of this we believe that you have come from God.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"31","text":" Jesus replied, \u201cDo you now believe?"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"32","text":"Look, a time is coming – and has come – when you will be scattered, each one to his own home, and I will be left alone. Yet I am not alone, because my Father is with me."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"16","verse":"33","text":"I have told you these things so that in me you may have peace. In the world you have trouble and suffering, but take courage – I have conquered the world.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"1","text":" When Jesus had finished saying these things, he looked upward to heaven and said, \u201cFather, the time has come. Glorify your Son, so that your Son may glorify you –"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"2","text":"just as you have given him authority over all humanity, so that he may give eternal life to everyone you have given him."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"3","text":"Now this is eternal life – that they know you, the only true God, and Jesus Christ, whom you sent."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"4","text":"I glorified you on earth by completing the work you gave me to do."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"5","text":"And now, Father, glorify me at your side with the glory I had with you before the world was created.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"6","text":" \u201cI have revealed your name to the men you gave me out of the world. They belonged to you, and you gave them to me, and they have obeyed your word."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"7","text":"Now they understand that everything you have given me comes from you,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"8","text":"because I have given them the words you have given me. They accepted them and really understand that I came from you, and they believed that you sent me."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"9","text":"I am praying on behalf of them. I am not praying on behalf of the world, but on behalf of those you have given me, because they belong to you."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"10","text":"Everything I have belongs to you, and everything you have belongs to me, and I have been glorified by them."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"11","text":"I am no longer in the world, but they are in the world, and I am coming to you. Holy Father, keep them safe in your name that you have given me, so that they may be one just as we are one."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"12","text":"When I was with them I kept them safe and watched over them in your name that you have given me. Not one of them was lost except the one destined for destruction, so that the scripture could be fulfilled."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"13","text":"But now I am coming to you, and I am saying these things in the world, so they may experience my joy completed in themselves."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"14","text":"I have given them your word, and the world has hated them, because they do not belong to the world, just as I do not belong to the world."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"15","text":"I am not asking you to take them out of the world, but that you keep them safe from the evil one."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"16","text":"They do not belong to the world just as I do not belong to the world."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"17","text":"Set them apart in the truth; your word is truth."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"18","text":"Just as you sent me into the world, so I sent them into the world."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"19","text":"And I set myself apart on their behalf, so that they too may be truly set apart.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"20","text":" \u201cI am not praying only on their behalf, but also on behalf of those who believe in me through their testimony,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"21","text":"that they will all be one, just as you, Father, are in me and I am in you. I pray that they will be in us, so that the world will believe that you sent me."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"22","text":"The glory you gave to me I have given to them, that they may be one just as we are one –"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"23","text":"I in them and you in me – that they may be completely one, so that the world will know that you sent me, and you have loved them just as you have loved me.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"24","text":" \u201cFather, I want those you have given me to be with me where I am, so that they can see my glory that you gave me because you loved me before the creation of the world."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"25","text":"Righteous Father, even if the world does not know you, I know you, and these men know that you sent me."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"17","verse":"26","text":"I made known your name to them, and I will continue to make it known, so that the love you have loved me with may be in them, and I may be in them.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"1","text":" When he had said these things, Jesus went out with his disciples across the Kidron Valley. There was an orchard there, and he and his disciples went into it."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"2","text":"(Now Judas, the one who betrayed him, knew the place too, because Jesus had met there many times with his disciples.)"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"3","text":"So Judas obtained a squad of soldiers and some officers of the chief priests and Pharisees. They came to the orchard with lanterns and torches and weapons.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"4","text":" Then Jesus, because he knew everything that was going to happen to him, came and asked them, \u201cWho are you looking for?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"5","text":"They replied, \u201cJesus the Nazarene.\u201d He told them, \u201cI am he.\u201d (Now Judas, the one who betrayed him, was standing there with them.)"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"6","text":"So when Jesus said to them, \u201cI am he,\u201d they retreated and fell to the ground."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"7","text":"Then Jesus asked them again, \u201cWho are you looking for?\u201d And they said, \u201cJesus the Nazarene.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"8","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cI told you that I am he. If you are looking for me, let these men go.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"9","text":"He said this to fulfill the word he had spoken, \u201cI have not lost a single one of those whom you gave me.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"10","text":" Then Simon Peter, who had a sword, pulled it out and struck the high priest\u2019s slave, cutting off his right ear. (Now the slave\u2019s name was Malchus.)"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"11","text":"But Jesus said to Peter, \u201cPut your sword back into its sheath! Am I not to drink the cup that the Father has given me?\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"12","text":" Then the squad of soldiers with their commanding officer and the officers of the Jewish leaders arrested Jesus and tied him up."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"13","text":"They brought him first to Annas, for he was the father-in-law of Caiaphas, who was high priest that year."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"14","text":"(Now it was Caiaphas who had advised the Jewish leaders that it was to their advantage that one man die for the people.)<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"15","text":" Simon Peter and another disciple followed them as they brought Jesus to Annas. (Now the other disciple was acquainted with the high priest, and he went with Jesus into the high priest\u2019s courtyard.)"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"16","text":"But Simon Peter was left standing outside by the door. So the other disciple who was acquainted with the high priest came out and spoke to the slave girl who watched the door, and brought Peter inside."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"17","text":"The girl who was the doorkeeper said to Peter, \u201cYou\u2019re not one of this man\u2019s disciples too, are you?\u201d He replied, \u201cI am not.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"18","text":"(Now the slaves and the guards were standing around a charcoal fire they had made, warming themselves because it was cold. Peter also was standing with them, warming himself.)<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"19","text":" While this was happening, the high priest questioned Jesus about his disciples and about his teaching."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"20","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cI have spoken publicly to the world. I always taught in the synagogues and in the temple courts, where all the Jewish people assemble together. I have said nothing in secret."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"21","text":"Why do you ask me? Ask those who heard what I said. They know what I said.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"22","text":"When Jesus had said this, one of the high priest\u2019s officers who stood nearby struck him on the face and said, \u201cIs that the way you answer the high priest?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"23","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cIf I have said something wrong, confirm what is wrong. But if I spoke correctly, why strike me?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"24","text":"Then Annas sent him, still tied up, to Caiaphas the high priest.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"25","text":" Meanwhile Simon Peter was standing in the courtyard warming himself. They said to him, \u201cYou aren\u2019t one of his disciples too, are you?\u201d Peter denied it: \u201cI am not!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"26","text":"One of the high priest\u2019s slaves, a relative of the man whose ear Peter had cut off, said, \u201cDid I not see you in the orchard with him?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"27","text":"Then Peter denied it again, and immediately a rooster crowed.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"28","text":" Then they brought Jesus from Caiaphas to the Roman governor\u2019s residence. (Now it was very early morning.) They did not go into the governor\u2019s residence so they would not be ceremonially defiled, but could eat the Passover meal."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"29","text":"So Pilate came outside to them and said, \u201cWhat accusation do you bring against this man?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"30","text":"They replied, \u201cIf this man were not a criminal, we would not have handed him over to you.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"31","text":" Pilate told them, \u201cTake him yourselves and pass judgment on him according to your own law!\u201d The Jewish leaders replied, \u201cWe cannot legally put anyone to death.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"32","text":"(This happened to fulfill the word Jesus had spoken when he indicated what kind of death he was going to die.)<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"33","text":" So Pilate went back into the governor\u2019s residence, summoned Jesus, and asked him, \u201cAre you the king of the Jews?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"34","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cAre you saying this on your own initiative, or have others told you about me?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"35","text":"Pilate answered, \u201cI am not a Jew, am I? Your own people and your chief priests handed you over to me. What have you done?\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"36","text":" Jesus replied, \u201cMy kingdom is not from this world. If my kingdom were from this world, my servants would be fighting to keep me from being handed over to the Jewish authorities. But as it is, my kingdom is not from here.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"37","text":"Then Pilate said, \u201cSo you are a king!\u201d Jesus replied, \u201cYou say that I am a king. For this reason I was born, and for this reason I came into the world – to testify to the truth. Everyone who belongs to the truth listens to my voice.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"38","text":"Pilate asked, \u201cWhat is truth?\u201d<\/p> When he had said this he went back outside to the Jewish leaders and announced, \u201cI find no basis for an accusation against him."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"39","text":"But it is your custom that I release one prisoner for you at the Passover. So do you want me to release for you the king of the Jews?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"18","verse":"40","text":"Then they shouted back, \u201cNot this man, but Barabbas!\u201d (Now Barabbas was a revolutionary.)<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"1","text":" Then Pilate took Jesus and had him flogged severely."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"2","text":"The soldiers braided a crown of thorns and put it on his head, and they clothed him in a purple robe."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"3","text":"They came up to him again and again and said, \u201cHail, king of the Jews!\u201d And they struck him repeatedly in the face.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"4","text":" Again Pilate went out and said to the Jewish leaders, \u201cLook, I am bringing him out to you, so that you may know that I find no reason for an accusation against him.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"5","text":"So Jesus came outside, wearing the crown of thorns and the purple robe. Pilate said to them, \u201cLook, here is the man!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"6","text":"When the chief priests and their officers saw him, they shouted out, \u201cCrucify him! Crucify him!\u201d Pilate said, \u201cYou take him and crucify him! Certainly I find no reason for an accusation against him!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"7","text":"The Jewish leaders replied, \u201cWe have a law, and according to our law he ought to die, because he claimed to be the Son of God!\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"8","text":" When Pilate heard what they said, he was more afraid than ever,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"9","text":"and he went back into the governor\u2019s residence and said to Jesus, \u201cWhere do you come from?\u201d But Jesus gave him no answer."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"10","text":"So Pilate said, \u201cDo you refuse to speak to me? Don\u2019t you know I have the authority to release you, and to crucify you?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"11","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cYou would have no authority over me at all, unless it was given to you from above. Therefore the one who handed me over to you is guilty of greater sin.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"12","text":" From this point on, Pilate tried to release him. But the Jewish leaders shouted out, \u201cIf you release this man, you are no friend of Caesar! Everyone who claims to be a king opposes Caesar!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"13","text":"When Pilate heard these words he brought Jesus outside and sat down on the judgment seat in the place called \u201cThe Stone Pavement\u201d (Gabbatha<\/i> in Aramaic)."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"14","text":"(Now it was the day of preparation for the Passover, about noon.) Pilate said to the Jewish leaders, \u201cLook, here is your king!\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"15","text":" Then they shouted out, \u201cAway with him! Away with him! Crucify him!\u201d Pilate asked, \u201cShall I crucify your king?\u201d The high priests replied, \u201cWe have no king except Caesar!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"16","text":"Then Pilate handed him over to them to be crucified.<\/p> So they took Jesus,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"17","text":"and carrying his own cross he went out to the place called \u201cThe Place of the Skull\u201d (called in Aramaic Golgotha<\/i>)."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"18","text":"There they crucified him along with two others, one on each side, with Jesus in the middle."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"19","text":"Pilate also had a notice written and fastened to the cross, which read: \u201cJesus the Nazarene, the king of the Jews.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"20","text":"Thus many of the Jewish residents of Jerusalem read this notice, because the place where Jesus was crucified was near the city, and the notice was written in Aramaic, Latin, and Greek."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"21","text":"Then the chief priests of the Jews said to Pilate, \u201cDo not write, \u2018The king of the Jews,\u2019 but rather, \u2018This man said, I am king of the Jews.\u2019\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"22","text":"Pilate answered, \u201cWhat I have written, I have written.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"23","text":" Now when the soldiers crucified Jesus, they took his clothes and made four shares, one for each soldier, and the tunic remained. (Now the tunic was seamless, woven from top to bottom as a single piece.)"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"24","text":"So the soldiers said to one another, \u201cLet\u2019s not tear it, but throw dice to see who will get it.\u201d This took place to fulfill the scripture that says, \u201cThey divided my garments among them, and for my clothing they threw dice<\/i><\/b>.\u201d So the soldiers did these things.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"25","text":" Now standing beside Jesus\u2019 cross were his mother, his mother\u2019s sister, Mary the wife of Clopas, and Mary Magdalene."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"26","text":"So when Jesus saw his mother and the disciple whom he loved standing there, he said to his mother, \u201cWoman, look, here is your son!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"27","text":"He then said to his disciple, \u201cLook, here is your mother!\u201d From that very time the disciple took her into his own home.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"28","text":" After this Jesus, realizing that by this time everything was completed, said (in order to fulfill the scripture), \u201cI am thirsty!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"29","text":"A jar full of sour wine was there, so they put a sponge soaked in sour wine on a branch of hyssop and lifted it to his mouth."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"30","text":"When he had received the sour wine, Jesus said, \u201cIt is completed!\u201d Then he bowed his head and gave up his spirit.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"31","text":" Then, because it was the day of preparation, so that the bodies should not stay on the crosses on the Sabbath (for that Sabbath was an especially important one), the Jewish leaders asked Pilate to have the victims\u2019 legs broken and the bodies taken down."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"32","text":"So the soldiers came and broke the legs of the two men who had been crucified with Jesus, first the one and then the other."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"33","text":"But when they came to Jesus and saw that he was already dead, they did not break his legs."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"34","text":"But one of the soldiers pierced his side with a spear, and blood and water flowed out immediately."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"35","text":"And the person who saw it has testified (and his testimony is true, and he knows that he is telling the truth), so that you also may believe."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"36","text":"For these things happened so that the scripture would be fulfilled, \u201cNot a bone of his will be broken<\/i><\/b>.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"37","text":"And again another scripture says, \u201cThey will look on the one whom they have pierced<\/i><\/b>.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"38","text":" After this, Joseph of Arimathea, a disciple of Jesus (but secretly, because he feared the Jewish leaders), asked Pilate if he could remove the body of Jesus. Pilate gave him permission, so he went and took the body away."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"39","text":"Nicodemus, the man who had previously come to Jesus at night, accompanied Joseph, carrying a mixture of myrrh and aloes weighing about seventy-five pounds."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"40","text":"Then they took Jesus\u2019 body and wrapped it, with the aromatic spices, in strips of linen cloth according to Jewish burial customs."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"41","text":"Now at the place where Jesus was crucified there was a garden, and in the garden was a new tomb where no one had yet been buried."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"19","verse":"42","text":"And so, because it was the Jewish day of preparation and the tomb was nearby, they placed Jesus\u2019 body there.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"1","text":" Now very early on the first day of the week, while it was still dark, Mary Magdalene came to the tomb and saw that the stone had been moved away from the entrance."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"2","text":"So she went running to Simon Peter and the other disciple whom Jesus loved and told them, \u201cThey have taken the Lord from the tomb, and we don\u2019t know where they have put him!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"3","text":"Then Peter and the other disciple set out to go to the tomb."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"4","text":"The two were running together, but the other disciple ran faster than Peter and reached the tomb first."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"5","text":"He bent down and saw the strips of linen cloth lying there, but he did not go in."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"6","text":"Then Simon Peter, who had been following him, arrived and went right into the tomb. He saw the strips of linen cloth lying there,"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"7","text":"and the face cloth, which had been around Jesus\u2019 head, not lying with the strips of linen cloth but rolled up in a place by itself."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"8","text":"Then the other disciple, who had reached the tomb first, came in, and he saw and believed."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"9","text":"(For they did not yet understand the scripture that Jesus must rise from the dead.)<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"10","text":" So the disciples went back to their homes."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"11","text":"But Mary stood outside the tomb weeping. As she wept, she bent down and looked into the tomb."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"12","text":"And she saw two angels in white sitting where Jesus\u2019 body had been lying, one at the head and one at the feet."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"13","text":"They said to her, \u201cWoman, why are you weeping?\u201d Mary replied, \u201cThey have taken my Lord away, and I do not know where they have put him!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"14","text":"When she had said this, she turned around and saw Jesus standing there, but she did not know that it was Jesus.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"15","text":" Jesus said to her, \u201cWoman, why are you weeping? Who are you looking for?\u201d Because she thought he was the gardener, she said to him, \u201cSir, if you have carried him away, tell me where you have put him, and I will take him.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"16","text":"Jesus said to her, \u201cMary.\u201d She turned and said to him in Aramaic, \u201cRabboni<\/i>\u201d (which means Teacher)."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"17","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cDo not touch me, for I have not yet ascended to my Father. Go to my brothers and tell them, \u2018I am ascending to my Father and your Father, to my God and your God.\u2019\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"18","text":"Mary Magdalene came and informed the disciples, \u201cI have seen the Lord!\u201d And she told them what Jesus had said to her.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"19","text":" On the evening of that day, the first day of the week, the disciples had gathered together and locked the doors of the place because they were afraid of the Jewish leaders. Jesus came and stood among them and said to them, \u201cPeace be with you.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"20","text":"When he had said this, he showed them his hands and his side. Then the disciples rejoiced when they saw the Lord."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"21","text":"So Jesus said to them again, \u201cPeace be with you. Just as the Father has sent me, I also send you.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"22","text":"And after he said this, he breathed on them and said, \u201cReceive the Holy Spirit."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"23","text":"If you forgive anyone\u2019s sins, they are forgiven; if you retain anyone\u2019s sins, they are retained.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"24","text":" Now Thomas (called Didymus), one of the twelve, was not with them when Jesus came."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"25","text":"The other disciples told him, \u201cWe have seen the Lord!\u201d But he replied, \u201cUnless I see the wounds from the nails in his hands, and put my finger into the wounds from the nails, and put my hand into his side, I will never believe it!\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"26","text":" Eight days later the disciples were again together in the house, and Thomas was with them. Although the doors were locked, Jesus came and stood among them and said, \u201cPeace be with you!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"27","text":"Then he said to Thomas, \u201cPut your finger here, and examine my hands. Extend your hand and put it into my side. Do not continue in your unbelief, but believe.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"28","text":"Thomas replied to him, \u201cMy Lord and my God!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"29","text":"Jesus said to him, \u201cHave you believed because you have seen me? Blessed are the people who have not seen and yet have believed.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"30","text":" Now Jesus performed many other miraculous signs in the presence of the disciples, which are not recorded in this book."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"20","verse":"31","text":"But these are recorded so that you may believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God, and that by believing you may have life in his name.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"1","text":" After this Jesus revealed himself again to the disciples by the Sea of Tiberias. Now this is how he did so."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"2","text":"Simon Peter, Thomas (called Didymus), Nathanael (who was from Cana in Galilee), the sons of Zebedee, and two other disciples of his were together."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"3","text":"Simon Peter told them, \u201cI am going fishing.\u201d \u201cWe will go with you,\u201d they replied. They went out and got into the boat, but that night they caught nothing.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"4","text":" When it was already very early morning, Jesus stood on the beach, but the disciples did not know that it was Jesus."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"5","text":"So Jesus said to them, \u201cChildren, you don\u2019t have any fish, do you?\u201d They replied, \u201cNo.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"6","text":"He told them, \u201cThrow your net on the right side of the boat, and you will find some.\u201d So they threw the net, and were not able to pull it in because of the large number of fish.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"7","text":" Then the disciple whom Jesus loved said to Peter, \u201cIt is the Lord!\u201d So Simon Peter, when he heard that it was the Lord, tucked in his outer garment (for he had nothing on underneath it), and plunged into the sea."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"8","text":"Meanwhile the other disciples came with the boat, dragging the net full of fish, for they were not far from land, only about a hundred yards.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"9","text":" When they got out on the beach, they saw a charcoal fire ready with a fish placed on it, and bread."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"10","text":"Jesus said, \u201cBring some of the fish you have just now caught.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"11","text":"So Simon Peter went aboard and pulled the net to shore. It was full of large fish, one hundred fifty-three, but although there were so many, the net was not torn."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"12","text":"\u201cCome, have breakfast,\u201d Jesus said. But none of the disciples dared to ask him, \u201cWho are you?\u201d because they knew it was the Lord."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"13","text":"Jesus came and took the bread and gave it to them, and did the same with the fish."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"14","text":"This was now the third time Jesus was revealed to the disciples after he was raised from the dead.<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"15","text":" Then when they had finished breakfast, Jesus said to Simon Peter, \u201cSimon, son of John, do you love me more than these do?\u201d He replied, \u201cYes, Lord, you know I love you.\u201d Jesus told him, \u201cFeed my lambs.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"16","text":"Jesus said a second time, \u201cSimon, son of John, do you love me?\u201d He replied, \u201cYes, Lord, you know I love you.\u201d Jesus told him, \u201cShepherd my sheep.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"17","text":"Jesus said a third time, \u201cSimon, son of John, do you love me?\u201d Peter was distressed that Jesus asked him a third time, \u201cDo you love me?\u201d and said, \u201cLord, you know everything. You know that I love you.\u201d Jesus replied, \u201cFeed my sheep."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"18","text":"I tell you the solemn truth, when you were young, you tied your clothes around you and went wherever you wanted, but when you are old, you will stretch out your hands, and others will tie you up and bring you where you do not want to go.\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"19","text":"(Now Jesus said this to indicate clearly by what kind of death Peter was going to glorify God.) After he said this, Jesus told Peter, \u201cFollow me.\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"20","text":" Peter turned around and saw the disciple whom Jesus loved following them. (This was the disciple who had leaned back against Jesus\u2019 chest at the meal and asked, \u201cLord, who is the one who is going to betray you?\u201d)"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"21","text":"So when Peter saw him, he asked Jesus, \u201cLord, what about him?\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"22","text":"Jesus replied, \u201cIf I want him to live until I come back, what concern is that of yours? You follow me!\u201d"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"23","text":"So the saying circulated among the brothers and sisters that this disciple was not going to die. But Jesus did not say to him that he was not going to die, but rather, \u201cIf I want him to live until I come back, what concern is that of yours?\u201d<\/p>"},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"24","text":" This is the disciple who testifies about these things and has written these things, and we know that his testimony is true."},{"bookname":"John","chapter":"21","verse":"25","text":"There are many other things that Jesus did. If every one of them were written down, I suppose the whole world would not have room for the books that would be written.<\/p>"}]}
